ou need to add a `key` prop. Hereâ€™s the relevant part of the code:\n\n```javascript\nthis.state.messages.forEach((msg, index) => {\n    messages.push(\n        <>\n            <Field label={msg.role}>\n                <TextArea\n                    style={{\n                        height: this.countLines(msg.content) * 1.4 + 2 + \"em\"\n                    }}\n                    monospace={true}\n                    showAll={true}\n                    value={msg.content}\n                    onChange={async (value) => {\n                        const newMessages = this.jsonCopy(this.state.messages);\n                        newMessages[index].content = value;\n\n                        const newDataset = this.jsonCopy(this.state.model);\n                        newDataset.json = JSON.stringify(newMessages);\n\n                        await this.updateState({\n                            model: newDataset,\n                            messages: newMessages\n                        });\n                    }}\n                />\n            </Field>\n            <Field>\n                <Button label=\"Resend\" onClick={this.resendClicked.bind(this, index)} />\n                <Button label=\"Remove\" onClick={this.removeClicked.bind(this, index)} />\n            </Field>\n        </>\n    );\n});\n```\n\nYou should change this to include a `key` prop. Since you are iterating over an array, you can use the `index` as a key (although using a unique identifier from the data is usually preferred if available). Hereâ€™s how you can modify it:\n\n```javascript\nthis.state.messages.forEach((msg, index) => {\n    messages.push(\n        <>\n            <Field label={msg.role} key={index}>\n                <TextArea\n                    style={{\n                        height: this.countLines(msg.content) * 1.4 + 2 + \"em\"\n                    }}\n                    monospace={true}\n                    showAll={true}\n                    value={msg.content}\n                    onChange={async (value) => {\n                        const newMessages = this.jsonCopy(this.state.messages);\n                        newMessages[index].content = value;\n\n                        const newDataset = this.jsonCopy(this.state.model);\n                        newDataset.json = JSON.stringify(newMessages);\n\n                        await this.updateState({\n                            model: newDataset,\n                            messages: newMessages\n                        });\n                    }}\n                />\n            </Field>\n            <Field>\n                <Button label=\"Resend\" onClick={this.resendClicked.bind(this, index)} />\n                <Button label=\"Remove\" onClick={this.removeClicked.bind(this, index)} />\n            </Field>\n        </>\n    );\n});\n```\n\nJust make sure that the `key` prop is unique for each item in the list to avoid potential issues with component state and rendering. In this case, using the `index` is acceptable, but if the messages had a unique identifier, that would be the best practice to use as a key.","refusal":null}]'),
